 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;NOTE 18&amp;#x2013; ACQUISITION OF CHERRYBERRY
 YOGLI MOGLI AND FUZZY PEACH&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3252&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: justify; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;On January 17
 2014
 U-Swirl entered into an Asset Purchase Agreement with CherryBerry and its affiliates (the &amp;#x201c;Cherryberry Purchase Agreement&amp;#x201d;)
 which was the franchisor of self-serve frozen yogurt caf&amp;eacute;s branded as &amp;#x201c;CherryBerry.&amp;#x201d; Pursuant to the CherryBerry Purchase Agreement
 U-Swirl purchased certain assets of CherryBerry used in its business of franchising frozen yogurt caf&amp;eacute;s
 including all of its franchise rights and one company-owned caf&amp;eacute;. The assets were acquired for approximately $4.25 million in cash and 4 million shares of U-Swirl common stock. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3254&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: justify; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;On January 17
 2014
 U-Swirl also entered into an Asset Purchase Agreement with Yogli Mogli LLC and its affiliates (the &amp;#x201c;Yogli Mogli Purchase Agreement&amp;#x201d;)
 which was the franchisor of self-serve frozen yogurt caf&amp;eacute;s branded as &amp;#x201c;Yogli Mogli.&amp;#x201d; Pursuant to the Yogli Mogli Purchase Agreement
 U-Swirl purchased certain assets of Yogli Mogli used in its business of franchising frozen yogurt caf&amp;eacute;s
 including all of its franchise rights and four company-owned caf&amp;eacute;s. The assets were acquired for approximately $2.15 million in cash and $200
000 in shares of U-Swirl common stock. During the year ended February 28
 2015
 U-Swirl assumed a net liability of $149
529 for an un-funded gift card liability related to Yogli-Mogli franchise operations. The Company has withheld the issuance of $200
000 in shares of U-Swirl common stock as a result of its realization of this unfunded liability. Management believes that is it unlikely that the common stock issuance contemplated by the Yogli Mogli Purchase Agreement is issued
 or that the gift card liability is funded. These facts have caused Management to revise the valuation of the Yogli Mogli purchase as reflected within this note to the consolidated financial statements.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3256&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: justify; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;On February 20
 2014
 U-Swirl entered into an Asset Purchase Agreement to acquire the business assets of Fuzzy Peach Franchising
 LLC. The acquisition of all intellectual property and worldwide franchise and license rights includes the rights associated with 17 Fuzzy Peach Frozen Yogurt stores. U-Swirl purchased the Fuzzy Peach Franchising
 LLC assets for $481
000 in cash paid at the time of closing
 plus an earn-out that could increase the purchase price by up to another $349
000 based upon royalty income generated by Fuzzy Peach stores over the next twelve months. During the year ended February 28
 2015
 we recorded a liability of $146
257 associated with this earn-out. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3258&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: justify; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;A preliminary purchase price allocation was completed at February 28
 2014 and a final measurement period was completed during the quarter ended February 28
 2015 when the fair value of consideration paid and contingent consideration were finalized. The foregoing resulted in a retrospective reallocation of these values reported at February 28
 2014. This reallocation did not result in any changes to operating results for FY 2014 because the adjustment to amortization resulting from the retrospective reallocation was immaterial. The final consideration value was allocated to assets acquired and liabilities assumed and a portion of the total purchase consideration was allocated to tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their respective fair values at the acquisition date. Prior year amounts were revised to reflect these changes as of the date of the acquisition
 resulting in reductions to Trademarks
 Franchise rights
 Non-competition agreements and Goodwill as of February 28
 2014. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3268&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: justify; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The following tables summarize the adjustments that were made to the preliminary purchase price allocation for the Yogli Mogli and CherryBerry acquisitions.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL4236&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 serif; WIDTH: 90%; MARGIN-RIGHT: 10%; TEXT-INDENT: 0px&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;

    &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3332&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: justify; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;The purchase price allocation
 including the fair value consideration paid
 contingent consideration
 the assets acquired and liabilities assumed and allocated a portion of the total purchase consideration to tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their respective fair values at the acquisition date. The excess of the total purchase consideration over the aggregate estimated fair values was recorded as goodwill. Goodwill represents the synergies that the Company believes will arise from the acquisition transactions. All of the goodwill generated in this acquisition is deductible for tax purposes. The following table summarizes the allocation of the purchase price to the fair value of the assets acquired and liabilities assumed:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;table id=&quot;TBL3363&quot; style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;Included in the purchase price allocation is an amount related to the fair value of the U-Swirl common stock issued as consideration for the acquisitions. The fair value of the securities was based on Financial Accounting Standard Board&amp;#x2019;s Accounting Standards Codification (&amp;#x201c;ASC&amp;#x201d;) 820-10-35-2
 Fair Value Measurements and Disclosures as &amp;#x201c;the price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date.&amp;#x201d; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3367&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: justify; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman

  &lt;/table&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p id=&quot;PARA3438&quot; style=&quot;TEXT-ALIGN: justify; MARGIN: 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman
 Times
 serif&quot;&gt;As a part of these acquisitions
 the Company recognized $124
551 and $786
475 as acquisition related costs in the line item &amp;#x201c;Restructuring and acquisition related charges&amp;#x201d; on the Statements of Income for the years ended February 28
 2015 and February 28
 2014
 respectively. The fair value of U-Swirl common stock was $0.24 and was determined by fair value measurement as defined by ASC 820-10-35-2. Fair Value Measurements and Disclosure is &amp;#x201c;the price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date.&amp;#x201d; The valuation was performed on a minority
 marketable basis. The Company performed this valuation because it did not believe that the quoted market price was indicative of fair value. Primarily the Company believed that the quoted market price did not accurately represent the present value of future cash flows associated with the acquisitions

							function toggleNextSibling (e) {
							if (e.nextSibling.style.display=='none') {
							e.nextSibling.style.display='block';
							} else {
							e.nextSibling.style.display='none';
							}
							}

Note 18 - Acquisition of Cherryberry
 Yogli Mogli
 and Fuzzy Peach

        

      






        
        


        
NOTE 18&#x2013; ACQUISITION OF CHERRYBERRY
On January 17
 2014
 U-Swirl entered into an Asset Purchase Agreement with CherryBerry and its affiliates (the &#x201c;Cherryberry Purchase Agreement&#x201d;)
 which was the franchisor of self-serve frozen yogurt caf&eacute;s branded as &#x201c;CherryBerry.&#x201d; Pursuant to the CherryBerry Purchase Agreement
 U-Swirl purchased certain assets of CherryBerry used in its business of franchising frozen yogurt caf&eacute;s
On January 17
 2014
 U-Swirl also entered into an Asset Purchase Agreement with Yogli Mogli LLC and its affiliates (the &#x201c;Yogli Mogli Purchase Agreement&#x201d;)
 which was the franchisor of self-serve frozen yogurt caf&eacute;s branded as &#x201c;Yogli Mogli.&#x201d; Pursuant to the Yogli Mogli Purchase Agreement
 U-Swirl purchased certain assets of Yogli Mogli used in its business of franchising frozen yogurt caf&eacute;s
 including all of its franchise rights and four company-owned caf&eacute;s. The assets were acquired for approximately $2.15 million in cash and $200
000 in shares of U-Swirl common stock. During the year ended February 28
 2015
 U-Swirl assumed a net liability of $149
529 for an un-funded gift card liability related to Yogli-Mogli franchise operations. The Company has withheld the issuance of $200
000 in shares of U-Swirl common stock as a result of its realization of this unfunded liability. Management believes that is it unlikely that the common stock issuance contemplated by the Yogli Mogli Purchase Agreement is issued
On February 20
 2014
 U-Swirl entered into an Asset Purchase Agreement to acquire the business assets of Fuzzy Peach Franchising
 LLC. The acquisition of all intellectual property and worldwide franchise and license rights includes the rights associated with 17 Fuzzy Peach Frozen Yogurt stores. U-Swirl purchased the Fuzzy Peach Franchising
 LLC assets for $481
000 in cash paid at the time of closing
 plus an earn-out that could increase the purchase price by up to another $349
000 based upon royalty income generated by Fuzzy Peach stores over the next twelve months. During the year ended February 28
 2015
 we recorded a liability of $146
A preliminary purchase price allocation was completed at February 28
 2014 and a final measurement period was completed during the quarter ended February 28
 2015 when the fair value of consideration paid and contingent consideration were finalized. The foregoing resulted in a retrospective reallocation of these values reported at February 28
 2014. This reallocation did not result in any changes to operating results for FY 2014 because the adjustment to amortization resulting from the retrospective reallocation was immaterial. The final consideration value was allocated to assets acquired and liabilities assumed and a portion of the total purchase consideration was allocated to tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their respective fair values at the acquisition date. Prior year amounts were revised to reflect these changes as of the date of the acquisition
 resulting in reductions to Trademarks
 Franchise rights
 Non-competition agreements and Goodwill as of February 28
 2014.

The purchase price allocation
 including the fair value consideration paid
 contingent consideration
 the assets acquired and liabilities assumed and allocated a portion of the total purchase consideration to tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their respective fair values at the acquisition date. The excess of the total purchase consideration over the aggregate estimated fair values was recorded as goodwill. Goodwill represents the synergies that the Company believes will arise from the acquisition transactions. All of the goodwill generated in this acquisition is deductible for tax purposes. The following table summarizes the allocation of the purchase price to the fair value of the assets acquired and liabilities assumed:

As a part of these acquisitions
 the Company recognized $124
551 and $786
475 as acquisition related costs in the line item &#x201c;Restructuring and acquisition related charges&#x201d; on the Statements of Income for the years ended February 28
 2015 and February 28
 2014
 respectively. The fair value of U-Swirl common stock was $0.24 and was determined by fair value measurement as defined by ASC 820-10-35-2. Fair Value Measurements and Disclosure is &#x201c;the price that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date.&#x201d; The valuation was performed on a minority
 marketable basis. The Company performed this valuation because it did not believe that the quoted market price was indicative of fair value. Primarily the Company believed that the quoted market price did not accurately represent the present value of future cash flows associated with the acquisitions
 or the dilutive effect of stock and convertible debt issued to fund these acquisitions.
